text.section:
The articles of incorporation shall set forth:
The name of the corporation that satisfies the requirements of KRS 14A.3-010;
The purpose for which it is formed;
The place, including the county, where its principal office will be located;
A reasonable description of the territory in which its operations are to be conducted;
The number of directors;
The names and post office addresses of the directors who are to manage the affairs of the corporation for the first year of its existence, or until the first meeting called to elect directors, or until the successors of the first directors are elected and have qualified;
The period limited for the duration of the corporation, or that the corporation is to be perpetual;
If the corporation is organized without capital stock, the terms upon which members may be admitted and the terms upon which their membership shall terminate;
If the corporation is organized with capital stock, the amount of the stock, the number of shares into which it is divided and the par value; and
If the capital stock is divided into common and preferred stock, as it may be, the number of shares to which preference is granted and the number of shares to which no preference is granted, and the nature and definite extent of the preference and privileges granted to each.
